data.title: Haylie Duff has a new show and an engagement ring!
data.meta_description: She has a new show and she just got engaged! Haylie Duff is having a really good April.
data.text:
She has a new show and she just got engaged! Haylie Duff is having a really good April.

While her sister is busy uncoupling, Haylie Duff is going to tie the knot with her boyfriend, Matt Rosenberg. The news was confirmed by Us Weekly and Haylie, who shared the excitement on Instagram on Thursday.

The news comes at a time when everything seems to be going right for the 29-year-old personality. She announced her Real Girl’s Kitchen show for the Cooking Channel and now she’s engaged to her boyfriend.

Haylie Duff’s Real Girl’s Kitchen cooks up LA love >>

The former 7th Heaven star wrote on her blog, “This week has seriously just become the best week of my life! As if announcing The Real Girl’s Kitchen tv show wasn’t enough, Matt just took me by total surprise and proposed…on April Fool’s Day of all days! The moment was genuine and sweet (like him!) and I couldn’t wait to say yes!”

On Instagram, she posted a photo with her arms wrapped around Rosenberg as well as showing off a gorgeous diamond ring on her left hand.

She captioned the photo, “The future Mrs.Rosenberg #Love @mr_sts.”

Haylie Duff’s healthy cooking must-haves >>

Even though little sister, Hilary, is in the midst of an amicable divorce from her husband, Mike Comrie, she took the time to tweet out sweet wishes to her big sister.

Haylie previously dated actor Nick Zano for three years. The couple split in November 2011.
